 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Warming increased the optimum water levels and decreased the critical water thresholds in the four 
  <span class="italic">Stipa</span> species. As warming, the critical water thresholds of the total biomass were −23% (T1) and −24% (T2) in 
  <span class="italic">S. breviflora</span>; −28% (T1) and + 26% (T2) in 
  <span class="italic">S. bungeana</span>; −27% (T1) and −36% (T2) in 
  <span class="italic">S. baicalensis</span>; and −12% (T1) and −17% (T2) in 
  <span class="italic">S. grandis</span> compared with the ambient water (Table 
  <a rid="ece35452-tbl-0007" ref-type="table" href="#ece35452-tbl-0007">7</a>).
 </p>
